	(331,241,'wp-svbtle-markdown','*For Immediate Release:*\r\n\r\n## Student’s Food Truck Finder Adds Chicago and Cleveland in National Launch\r\n\r\nSaint Louis – July 17, 2012 –Today [Food Trucks Near Me](http://www.FoodTrucksNearMe.com) adds new pages for Cleveland and Chicago in a national launch. Washington University in St. Louis Senior Philip Thomas designed the original St. Louis website to make finding food trucks easy. Following its successful local launch last month, the updated site expands to the Cleveland and Chicago markets.\r\n\r\nThe website allows users to find food trucks’ locations and menus via computer or smartphone. Today’s update also allows food truck owners to purchase priority placement for a monthly fee.\r\n\r\n[Food Trucks Near Me](http://www.FoodTrucksNearMe.com) plans to continue adding new cities in the coming month. The site updates constantly with the latest news from food trucks and is available at [www.FoodTrucksNearMe.com](http://www.foodtrucksnearme.com).\r\n\r\nWebsite: 	[www.FoodTrucksNearMe.com](http://www.foodtrucksnearme.com)\r\n\r\nTwitter: [@FoodTrucksNear](http://twitter.com/foodtrucksnear)\r\n\r\nContact:	\r\nPhilip I. Thomas, Founder\r\n[PR@FoodTrucksNearMe.com](mailto:pr@foodtrucksnearme.com)\r\nFood Trucks Near Me LLC\r\n\r\n\r\n###'),
