	(11,1,'2012-07-09 01:40:21','2012-07-09 01:40:21','This is an example page. It\'s different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:\n\n<blockquote>Hi there! I\'m a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my blog. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like pi&#241;a coladas. (And gettin\' caught in the rain.)</blockquote>\n\n...or something like this:\n\n<blockquote>The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickies to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.</blockquote>\n\nAs a new WordPress user, you should go to <a href=\"http://www.foodtrucksnearme.com/blog/wp-admin/\">your dashboard</a> to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!','Sample Page','','publish','open','open','','sample-page','','','2012-07-09 01:40:21','2012-07-09 01:40:21','',0,'http://www.foodtrucksnearme.com/blog/?page_id=2',0,'page','',0),
	(291,1,'2012-07-12 05:45:33','2012-07-12 05:45:33','<p><em>For Immediate Release:</em></p>\n\n<h2>Student\'s Food Truck Website Goes National</h2>\n\n<p>Saint Louis – July 12, 2012 – Aiming to make access to St. Louis food trucks easier, WashU Senior <a href=\"http://philipithomas.com\">Philip Thomas</a> launched <a href=\"http://foodtruckstl.org\">Food Truck STL</a>, a website to track up-to-the-minute updates from local food trucks.  \"He\'s a solutions kind of guy,\" said Randi Naughton during an interview of Philip on <a href=\"http://fox2now.com/2012/07/02/student-creates-one-stop-food-truck-website/#ooid=AyZWJhNTomKhB7a53eJEQfWV2a0qKpzz\">Fox 2 News in the Morning</a>. Today Food Truck STL becomes <a href=\"http://foodtrucksnearme.com\">Food Trucks Near Me</a>, with new pages for food trucks in Chicago and Cleveland. </p>\n\n<p>\"Thousands have already used the St. Louis site, and now I begin expanding with pages for Chicago and Cleveland,\" remarked Philip. The interface makes access to the twitter updates, menus, websites, and more information about local food trucks easy to read. The mobile-compatible website is accompanied by Twitter and Facebook profiles for each city that combine updates from listed food trucks.  </p>\n\n<p>In addition, the new Food Trucks Near Me includes <a href=\"http://foodtrucksnearme.com/about#priority\">priority listings</a> in each city to allow trucks to be in the first row of their city.  </p>\n\n<p>Food Trucks Near Me aims to continue engaging food lovers by expanding to new cities and improving functionality</p>\n\n<p>Website: http://FoodTrucksNearMe.com\nTwitter: http://twitter.com/NearFoodTrucks</p>\n\n<p>Contact:\nPhilip I. Thomas, Founder\nPhilip@FoodTrucksNearMe.com\nFood Trucks Near Me LLC</p>\n\n<h2>#</h2>\n','[Press Release] Student\'s Food Truck Website Goes National','','inherit','open','open','','241-revision-5','','','2012-07-12 05:45:33','2012-07-12 05:45:33','',241,'http://www.foodtrucksnearme.com/blog/?p=291',