	(151,1,'2012-07-10 22:14:34','2012-07-10 22:14:34','<i>For Immediate Release:</i>\r\n\r\n<h2>Food Truck Dashboard Launched by WashU Senior</h2>\r\n\r\nSaint Louis – June 29, 2012 – While having trouble finding his favorite taco truck for lunch, WashU senior Philip I. Thomas envisioned a simple solution to track the locations of St. Louis food trucks. Frustrated and hungry, he decided to build a website himself.\r\n\r\nOn June 28, two days after coming up with the idea, FoodTruckSTL.org launched. Its simple, smartphone-compatible layout shares live updates on the locations of 30 local food trucks with links to their menus. Its co-launched @FoodTruckSTL Twitter feed collects and shares updates from these sites in one location. “Food Truck STL helps the community support local small businesses while enjoying delicious food,” says Philip. With well over 500 visits in the few hours after launch, Philip plans to expand to other cities in the coming weeks.\r\n\r\nWebsite: <a href=\"http://foodtruckstl.org\">http://FoodTruckSTL.org</a>\r\nTwitter: <a href=\"http://twitter.com/foodtruckstl\">http://twitter.com/FoodTruckSTL</a>\r\n\r\nContact\r\nPhilip I. Thomas\r\nInquiries@SapientiaMedia.com\r\nSapientia Media LLC\r\n\r\n###','[Press Release] Food Truck Dashboard Launched by WashU Senior','','publish','open','open','','press-release-food-truck-dashboard-launched-by-washu-senior','','','2012-07-10 22:14:34','2012-07-10 22:14:34','',0,'http://www.foodtrucksnearme.com/blog/?p=151',0,'post','',0),
